## Objective

Add Expo Application Services (EAS) configuration to the mobile project.
This enables cloud builds without any local development environment.

No new features. No backend changes. Pure build configuration.

---

## Context to load

- `mobile/app.json`
- `mobile/package.json`
- `mobile/app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx`

---

## What to Build

### 1. `mobile/eas.json`

```json
{
  "cli": {
    "version": ">= 10.0.0"
  },
  "build": {
    "development": {
      "developmentClient": false,
      "distribution": "internal",
      "ios": {
        "simulator": false
      },
      "env": {
        "EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL": "https://flipper-production-dca0.up.railway.app/api/v1"
      }
    },
    "preview": {
      "developmentClient": false,
      "distribution": "internal",
      "ios": {
        "simulator": false
      },
      "env": {
        "EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL": "https://flipper-production-dca0.up.railway.app/api/v1"
      }
    },
    "production": {
      "distribution": "store",
      "env": {
        "EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL": "https://flipper-production-dca0.up.railway.app/api/v1"
      }
    }
  },
  "submit": {
    "production": {}
  }
}
```

### 2. Update `mobile/app.json`

Add `owner` field and `extra` config for EAS:

```json
{
  "expo": {
    "name": "Flipper",
    "slug": "flipper",
    "owner": "flipper-app",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "orientation": "portrait",
    "userInterfaceStyle": "light",
    "icon": "./assets/icon.png",
    "splash": {
      "image": "./assets/splash.png",
      "backgroundColor": "#FFFFFF"
    },
    "ios": {
      "bundleIdentifier": "com.flipper.app",
      "supportsTablet": false
    },
    "plugins": [
      "expo-router",
      "expo-font",
      [
        "expo-notifications",
        {
          "icon": "./assets/icon.png",
          "color": "#00C853"
        }
      ]
    ],
    "scheme": "flipper",
    "extra": {
      "eas": {
        "projectId": "REPLACE_WITH_EAS_PROJECT_ID"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Note: `REPLACE_WITH_EAS_PROJECT_ID` is a placeholder.
The real project ID comes from expo.dev after the project
is created there. This will be filled in manually.

### 3. Update `mobile/package.json`

Add EAS CLI as a dev dependency:

```json
{
  "devDependencies": {
    "eas-cli": "^10.0.0"
  }
}
```

Also add a build script:

```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "start": "expo start",
    "build:preview": "eas build --platform ios --profile preview",
    "build:production": "eas build --platform ios --profile production"
  }
}
```

### 4. Create `mobile/assets/icon.png` and `mobile/assets/splash.png`

Generate simple placeholder assets:
- `icon.png` — 1024x1024px, white background, black "F" in Inter Bold, centred
- `splash.png` — 1284x2778px, white background, "Flipper" in Inter Bold 48sp, centred, with green `#00C853` dot before the F

If image generation is not possible, create a note file:
`mobile/assets/ASSETS_NEEDED.md` explaining the required dimensions
so they can be created manually or via a design tool.

